# LocalSend Electron Project Rules

## Required Reading

Before starting any task, please read the following documents:

1. **ARCHITECTURE.md** - Architecture documentation (required)
2. **AGENTS.md** - AI Agent guide
3. **apps/electron-app/AGENTS.md** - Electron app development guide

## Project Overview

This is an Electron-based LocalSend client implementation using Rush monorepo architecture.

## Core Technologies

- Rush 5.166.0 + pnpm (Monorepo)
- Electron 26 (Desktop framework)
- React 18 + TypeScript (Frontend)
- Vite 5 (Build tool)
- UnoCSS (Styling)
- Hono (HTTP server)
- electron-log (Logging)

## Key Ports

- 53317: LocalSend protocol port (TCP/HTTPS + UDP multicast)

## Development Commands

```bash
rush install    # Install dependencies
rush build      # Build all projects
cd apps/electron-app && yarn dev  # Development mode
```

## Code Guidelines

1. Use TypeScript
2. Use UnoCSS atomic class names
3. Main process logging uses electron-log
4. Renderer process logging uses src/utils/logger.ts
